      <intermediateExchange id="c2de85bd-8d0a-5c84-b893-8d2ecd0b2091" unitId="980b811e-3905-4797-82a5-173f5568bc7e" amount="2.34" intermediateExchangeId="63ead738-2005-498c-8359-7f65c134a1a4" activityLinkId="8a4d3237-2b7f-52c5-af32-a08b2c4ed324">
        <name xml:lang="en">heat, from steam, in chemical industry</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">MJ</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">A value of 2 MJ of steam was reported by Kim and Overcash (2003), which they also reported the potential energy recovery of 1.11 MJ per kg of N, N-dimethylformamide produced. At the same time, a value of 2.34 MJ of steam input was calculated based on data from an Indian plant (DSIR,1993. We, here, use the most conservative estimate of steam input. 
References: 
Kim, Seungdo, and Michael Overcash "Energy in chemical manufacturing processes: gate‐to‐gate information for life cycle assessment." Journal of Chemical Technology &amp; Biotechnology: International Research in Process, Environmental &amp; Clean Technology 78.9 (2003)
DSIR 1993: "Department of Scientific and Industrial Research; Technology in Indian Di-Mythyl Formamide Industry Technical Report No. 1004, New Deöhi 1993. "Depeartment of Scientific and Industrial Research: Technology in Indian Di-Methyl Formamide Industry Technical Report No.104. New Delhi 1993"</comment>
